ValueAnimation, which derives from Resources, does not override the virtual `BeginLoad()` method instead it implements a non-virtual function `Load()` of Resource class. Due to this, value animations cannot be loaded from resource file into a ValueAnimation object. 
Funny enough, the codes in `Load()`, I suppose, are meant to be the codes in `BeginLoad()`.
Implementing `BeginLoad()` method in the source solves this problem. 

```
bool ValueAnimation::BeginLoad(Deserializer& source)
{
    XMLFile xmlFile(context_);
    if (!xmlFile.Load(source))
    return false;

    return LoadXML(xmlFile.GetRoot());
}
```

